 772.2]}, {"text": "ratio. *P < 0.05; **P < 0.01.", "bbox": [198.9, 768.7, 324.8, 786.0]}, {"text": "relationship in the multiple regression model with the prevalence of myopia and the mean SER. Because studies", "bbox": [198.9, 822.6, 708.9, 838.2]}, {"text": "have suggested that the time spent near work is significantly associated with AL46,47, we might infer that visual", "bbox": [198.9, 835.4, 708.9, 850.9]}, {"text": "behavioural factors, such as the time spent near work, are more likely to affect the AL, whereas nutrition intake,", "bbox": [198.9, 848.2, 709.0, 863.7]}, {"text": "such as breast milk, in early life may have a greater effect on the SER. Nutritional and visual behavioural factors", "bbox": [198.9, 861.0, 709.0, 876.5]}, {"text": "might have different impacts on eye development. This result was also supported by the effect of DHA and ARA", "bbox": [198.9, 873.8, 709.0, 889.3]}, {"text": "in breast milk on retinal and neural development compared with the effect on the AL. However, more details need", "bbox": [198.9, 886.5, 708.8, 902.1]}, {"text": "to be confirmed in further studies.", "bbox": [198.9, 899.3, 355.3, 914.8]}, {"text": "Potential limitations of our study should be noted. First, data on breastfeeding and myopia-related factors", "bbox": [214.3, 912.1, 709.0, 927.6]}, {"text": "were reported by parents in this questionnaire a few years after the events occurred. Although this method has", "bbox": [198.9, 924.9, 709.0, 940.4]}, {"text": "SCieNTifiC RepoRtS | (2018) 8:10025 | DOI:10.1038/s41598-018-27878-0 5", "bbox": [52.1, 964.7, 708.9, 979.9]}]}